    <text>
        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Balto. Febr 17th<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>Esteemed friend.<lb/></p>
            <p>Pardon my seeming neglect in waiting till<lb/> to&#45;day to attend to a duty I should have seen to<lb/> before&#59; but my d. wife&#39;s indisposition prevented<lb/> my leaving the house daily before  four o&#39;clock<lb/> &#38; then it is too late for the Post Office.<lb/></p>
            <p>Enclosed please find money order for &#36; 6.00&#44;<lb/> which I take the liberty to forward for the<lb/> Expenses i&#91;overwritten&#58; e&#93;ncurred by your recent trip to<lb/> this city&#44; wherever I go&#44; I hear the pro&#45;<lb/>found satisfaction and unanimous praise<lb/> your address has created here&#44; I hope and<lb/>  sincerely pray that the response to your<lb/> able efforts will be in proportion to the<lb/> sincerity of your eloquence and the<lb/> approbation of the public. Thus far<lb/> I received no indication of such&#44; beyond<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>what Mr Friedenwald told me&#44;<lb/> that several members of his family<lb/> will do justice to the cause.<lb/> I will announce from the pulp&#91;&#94;&#93;it<lb/> next Sabbath&#44; that I will receive<lb/> for further transmission any sums<lb/> or promises to subscription for the<lb/> fund. I shall write to NY for<lb/> more circulars if they can be<lb/> obtained &#38; if I am to go to Washing&#45;<lb/>ton&#44; I shall <del>f</del> want some for distri&#45;<lb/>bution there.<lb/></p>
            <p>If I can be of any service to you&#44; I <lb/> will only be too glad to lend you my<lb/>assistance and if your leisure time<lb/> allows to communicate on the subject&#44; be<lb/> most grateful for any information&#91;.&#93;<lb/></p>
            <p>My d. wife  th. G. is feeling much better<lb/> to&#45;day &#38; begs to be kindly remembered.<lb/>
                With best greetings I am<lb/>
                fraternally yours<lb/>
                &#91;&#63;&#93; Schneeberger&#91;&#63;&#93;</p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>P.S. I just had a talk with Dr. Friedenwald<lb/> who was here on a professional visit&#8212;he told<lb/> me what he and others of his family are<lb/> ready to contribute &#38; we resolved to<lb/> organize a local Committee consisting<lb/> of influential men of the various Congre&#45;<lb/>gations together with Mr. Mendez Cohen&#44;<lb/> Dr. F &#38; myself and endeavor to<lb/> canvass the city to get subscriptions<lb/> and members for the Seminary&#8212;I <lb/> think the plan a good one and if the<lb/> same could be done elsewhere&#44; we could<lb/> easier approach the masses&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            </body>
